---
description: Use shadcn/ui for frontend UI work
globs: apps/web/**/*.{ts,tsx,css}
alwaysApply: false
---

# shadcn/ui

- Use shadcn/ui components by default for frontend UI where practical.
- If shadcn is not configured yet, initialize it before building new UI features.
- Prefer shadcn components and local `components/ui` patterns over custom component styling.
- Use Tailwind CSS tokens and CSS variables from the shadcn theme once configured.
- Add shadcn components with `npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]`.

# blocks.so

- Use blocks.so through the shadcn registry only for AI interaction UI where it clearly fits.
- Add the `@blocks-so` registry only when a selected block is needed.
- Add blocks with `npx shadcn@latest add @blocks-so/[component-name]`.
